@* Deliberately unaware of the cascading value. This component has no [CascadingParameter],
   no [Parameter] related to UserContext or IsAdmin, and no @code logic referencing either.
   It exists solely to demonstrate that intermediate layers in a component tree do not need
   to know about or relay a cascading value — the framework delivers it directly to any
   descendant that declares [CascadingParameter], skipping all layers in between.
   Contrast with the TagSection/TagPicker bubbling pattern elsewhere in this project, where
   every layer must explicitly participate to pass a value downward. *@

<div class="border border-secondary rounded p-3 mb-3">
    <p class="text-muted small mb-2">Middle layer (no knowledge of cascading value)</p>
    @ChildContent
</div>

@code {
    [Parameter] public RenderFragment? ChildContent { get; set; }
}
